screen-translator (1.5.8-1) stable; urgency=low

  * Hybrid Wayland fix: use GDK_BACKEND=x11 (XWayland) for window positioning
    while keeping wl-paste for clipboard detection — best of both approaches
  * Fixed popup always showing at same location (Wayland POPUP windows need parent)
  * Fixed double-translation trigger when primary and clipboard both fire same text
  * Simplified popup positioning: show_all() before measuring allocated size

 -- sonnn <sonnn@localhost>  Fri, 29 May 2026 17:44:00 +0700

screen-translator (1.5.7-1) stable; urgency=low

  * Complete rewrite of clipboard monitor for Wayland compatibility
  * On Wayland: polls wl-paste (wl-clipboard) every 500ms for PRIMARY and CLIPBOARD
  * On X11: retains GTK owner-change signals + 1s polling fallback
  * Added wl-clipboard to Recommends in debian/control

